@page "/module3-challenge"
@using BlazorWorkshopApp.Components;

<PageTitle>Unraveling the Mystery: Dev Container Detective Work</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1>Unraveling the Mystery: Dev Container Detective Work</h1>
    
    <p>Welcome to your next challenge, where detective skills meet development environments. A hidden alteration lies within, waiting to be discovered and rectified. Are you ready to embark on this investigative journey?</p>
    
    <!-- The Mysterious Beginning -->
    <h2>1: The Mysterious Beginning</h2>
    <CollapsibleSection>
    <p>Initiate your quest by triggering a hidden task designed to simulate a real-world development hiccup.</p>
    <h3>Initiating the Error:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Access the Task Runner:</strong> Open Visual Studio Code's task runner by pressing <code>Ctrl+Shift+B</code> (or <code>Cmd+Shift+B</code> on macOS), bringing forth the interface that houses various pre-configured tasks.</li>
        <li><strong>Select the Task:</strong> From the list of available tasks, select <strong>"MODULE 3: Introduce Dev Container Error"</strong>. This task is engineered to subtly alter your dev container configuration, mimicking the nuances of real-world development scenarios.</li>
    </ol>
    </CollapsibleSection>

    <!-- Encounter with the Unexpected -->
    <h2>2: Encounter with the Unexpected</h2>
    <CollapsibleSection>
    <p>With the stage set, proceed to rebuild your dev container. Watch closely for unexpected behavior, marking the start of your detective work.</p>
    </CollapsibleSection>

    <!-- Choosing the Path of Recovery -->
    <h2>3: Choosing the Path of Recovery</h2>
    <CollapsibleSection>
    <p>In the face of adversity, the option to <strong>Edit in Recovery Mode</strong> becomes your gateway to investigation. This special mode allows you to access and edit your configurations, even when the primary build fails.</p>
    </CollapsibleSection>

    <!-- The Investigation Begins -->
    <h2>4: The Investigation Begins</h2>
    <CollapsibleSection>
    <p>Dive into the logs and outputs that detail the build process. Here, amidst the technical verbosity, lies the clue to solving the mystery.</p>
    </CollapsibleSection>

    <!-- Piecing Together the Clues -->
    <h2>5: Piecing Together the Clues</h2>
    <CollapsibleSection>
    <p>Armed with observations, begin to piece together the evidence. Your goal is to identify the misconfiguration that led to the build error.</p>
    </CollapsibleSection>

    <!-- Eureka: The Moment of Discovery -->
    <h2>6: Eureka -The Moment of Discovery</h2>
    <CollapsibleSection>
    <p>With all clues in hand, the moment of revelation is upon you. Apply your findings, adjusting the dev container configuration to resolve the build error.</p>
    </CollapsibleSection>

    <!-- Reflection and Mastery -->
    <h2>7: Reflection and Mastery</h2>
    <p>As you emerge victorious, take a moment to reflect on the journey and the lessons learned. Each challenge you overcome furthers your mastery of development environments.</p>
    
</div>

